Text: I love his cute Pomeranian😍😍😍😍, I have the same type of Pomeranian name "Buster" who was gifted to me from a really close friend of mine, whom she gotten him from a military family who couldn't take him on their relocation overseas. So they given him to her, but she couldn't keep him for too long, because she had other dogs , that wasn't too kind to Buster. They would try to fight with him and he was still a bit of a baby, so she had to keep him in a different room. Long story short she was going to put him in a shelter but thought of me during the time I and my husband just bought and moved into our first home 3 1/2 years ago. She sent me a picture of him and explained everything and the situation that "Buster" has went through and she didn't want to place him in a shelter and she knew I always wanted a dog, but couldn't have one due to our landlord restrictions with animals in the home before buying our first home(VERY LONG and HARD PROCESS) but thats the stepping stone of beginning to purchase a home😥😥😥😥. So we accepted him and she told me that we could change his given name "Buster". I told her it seems to not be right, because he was always called "Buster" and he knew his name is Buster, so we stuck with his given name. He been with us now the same amount years we bought our first home and he has been our blessing along with our 3 children. The love he shows us and the cute way he tilt his head when we talk to him.......as if he was a human being in a different life perhaps and his affection when he knows when you're sad and he trys to cheer you up by doing something silly or cuddle up next to you. We love him SO much and we wouldn't trade him for the world. 😌😌😌😏😏😏😏
